1. Check Buildings, Grounds, Fences and Foliage for plant growth or material impeding water drainage, damaging fence lines or preventing entrance to station.
2. Check floodlights and emergency lighting and see if there are any objects blocking sources of light in and around the building. Are all areas of the station well-lit and easy to navigate?
3. Check that all substation Windows, Doors, and Gates are in proper working order and they are locked at all times.
4. Check the Visitor's Record to see that it's up to date, properly filled out and organized and that there enough sheets and open spaces.
5. Check to see that the ladders on site are stored properly and locked, and are the correct numbers, lengths, and types.
6. Make sure the station mats and driveways are clear of debris (including snow and leaf accumulation). There must be ease of access throughout the station lot and mats.
